<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-07-20T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-07-20T00:00:00-05:00" n="726" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d726">
                                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.00119 Potsdam/7–2045</note>
                                <head>No. 726<lb/><hi rend="italic">Memorandum by the First
                                        Secretary of Embassy in Portugal</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_CCW1"><hi rend="italic">Cannon</hi></persName>)<note n="1" xml:id="d726fn1">Printed
                                        from a carbon copy on which there is an uncertified typed
                                        signature.</note></head>
                                <opener>
                                    <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Potsdam</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-07-20">July 20,
                                            1945</date>.</dateline>
                                </opener>
                                <p rend="center"><hi rend="smallcaps">Memorandum</hi></p>
                                <p>In presenting this paper<note n="2" xml:id="d726fn2"><ref target="#d1091">Document No. 1091</ref>.</note> the
                                    Secretary may wish orally to restate the interest of the United
                                    States Government in the early admission of Italy to the United
                                    Nations Organization, and to observe that this matter is being
                                    handled separately by a Sub-Committee.</p>
                                <closer><signed><persName corresp="#p_CCW1"><hi rend="smallcaps">Cavendish W.
                                    Cannon</hi></persName></signed></closer>
                            </div>
                            </body></text></TEI>